        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 4:50PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 449 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Swartz Creek, or near Flushing, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Flint, Grand Blanc, Davison, Burton, Swartz Creek, Crossroads
Village, Beecher, Genesee, and Atlas.

People attending Everett Cummings Center  should seek safe shelter
immediately!
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
